toatoa
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an endemic shrub-like bush.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Haloragis erecta</i> a perennial shrubby bush aka Toatoa, fire weed, shrubby haloragis, not to be confused with the three toatoa pine species.
